Which Azure VPN Gateway configuration provides the most flexibility and best performance?', '["Basic SKU with Policy-based VPN","VpnGw1 SKU with Route-based VPN and BGP enabled","Standard SKU with Policy-based VPN and BGP enabled","VpnGw2 SKU with Policy-based VPN"]', '[1]', 'VpnGw1 with Route-based VPN and BGP provides the most flexibility. Route-based VPNs support multiple tunnels, point-to-site connections, and better performance. BGP enables dynamic routing and automatic failover. Basic SKU doesn''t support BGP.', '{"correct":"VpnGw1 SKU with Route-based VPN and BGP is optimal because: 1) Route-based VPNs offer more flexibility than policy-based (support for point-to-site, multiple site-to-site connections, and transit routing), 2) BGP provides dynamic routing with automatic failover and load balancing, 3) VpnGw1 offers better performance than Basic while being cost-effective compared to VpnGw2.","why_others_wrong":{"0":"Basic SKU doesn''t support BGP routing, which limits dynamic routing capabilities and automatic failover. It also has lower throughput limits.","2":"Standard SKU with Policy-based VPN is less flexible than Route-based VPN and doesn''t support point-to-site connections or multiple site-to-site tunnels.","3":"VpnGw2 with Policy-based VPN doesn''t utilize the device''s route-based capabilities and BGP support, making it less flexible and not cost-effective."}}', '{"title":"VPN Gateway design - Azure VPN Gateway","url":"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/vpn-gateway/design"}', '2025-08-17T02:46:25.562325+00:00', '2025-08-17T02:46:25.562325+00:00', TRUE) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
