Where will traffic to 10.1.1.10 be routed?', '["Internet (system route)","Virtual Appliance at 10.0.1.4","VNet Gateway","ExpressRoute connection"]', '[3]', 'Route priority: UDR > BGP > System routes. Among overlapping routes, more specific (longer prefix) takes precedence. 10.1.1.0/25 (BGP) is more specific than 10.1.1.0/24 (UDR), so traffic goes to ExpressRoute.', '{"correct":"Azure routing follows a priority order: User Defined Routes (UDR) > BGP routes > System routes. However, among routes of the same type, the most specific route (longest prefix match) wins. The BGP route 10.1.1.0/25 (/25 = 25-bit subnet mask) is more specific than the UDR route 10.1.1.0/24 (/24 = 24-bit subnet mask). Since 10.1.1.10 falls within both ranges but the BGP route is more specific, traffic will be routed to the ExpressRoute connection.","why_others_wrong":{"0":"The system route 0.0.0.0/0 has the lowest priority and only applies when no more specific routes match.","1":"The UDR for 10.1.0.0/16 does match the destination, but the more specific BGP route 10.1.1.0/25 takes precedence.","2":"The UDR for 10.1.1.0/24 matches but is less specific than the BGP route 10.1.1.0/25, so the BGP route is chosen."}}', '{"title":"Virtual network traffic routing - Azure Virtual Network","url":"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-network/virtual-networks-udr-overview"}', '2025-08-17T02:46:25.562325+00:00', '2025-08-17T02:46:25.562325+00:00', TRUE) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
