What type of routing should you configure?', '["Multi-site routing","Path-based routing","URL rewrite routing","Priority-based routing"]', '[1]', 'Path-based routing allows you to route requests to different backend pools based on URL paths. This is ideal for routing /api/* and /images/* to different destinations.', '{"correct":"Path-based routing in Application Gateway examines the URL path of incoming requests and routes them to different backend pools based on configured path rules. This feature is specifically designed for scenarios where different parts of an application (like API endpoints, static content, and main web content) need to be served by different backend services.","why_others_wrong":{"0":"Multi-site routing routes traffic based on the hostname/domain, not URL paths. It''s used when hosting multiple websites on the same Application Gateway.","2":"URL rewrite modifies the URL before sending it to backends but doesn''t provide routing decisions based on paths.","3":"Priority-based routing is not a standard Application Gateway feature. Routing decisions are based on rules matching, not priorities."}}', '{"title":"Application Gateway path-based routing","url":"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/application-gateway/url-route-overview"}', '2025-08-17T02:46:25.562325+00:00', '2025-08-17T02:46:25.562325+00:00', TRUE) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
